 More than 3 000 runners will take part in the marathon this Saturday. The 50km ultra marathon runner, finishing at Loskop Dam, will start at 06:00. The 21km participants of the Wild Challenge, hosted by the Loskop Nature Reserve, will start at 06:30. The 4,9km Save the Rhino fun walk will kick off at 06:45 at the nature reserve. No cyclists will be allowed on the N11, apart from officials accompanying runners.
Only official vehicles marked clearly will be allowed on the route. Rolling road openings on the N11 will commence once the last athletes have passed certain points. The N11 will reopen entirely at 13:00. •Motorists can use the alternative Stoffberg Road to Limpopo.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za